# {{.ProjectName}}

Claude executable plugin generated by [plugin-kit-ai](https://github.com/777genius/plugin-kit-ai) `init`.

This local plugin starter is the fastest path when you want repo-local integration and quick iteration in `{{.Runtime}}`.
It is a stable supported path for Python and Node teams, not a second-class fallback.
{{- if .IsCustomLogicTemplate }}

This is the advanced custom-logic path. Choose it when the plugin's value lives in your runtime code, hooks, or orchestration logic instead of only wiring an existing service or local tool.

## What You Edit First

- `src/plugin.yaml`: shared plugin identity and target scope
- `src/launcher.yaml`: runtime and entrypoint metadata
- `src/main.{{if eq .Runtime "python"}}py{{else if eq .Runtime "node"}}{{if .TypeScript}}ts{{else}}mjs{{end}}{{else}}sh{{end}}` or `scripts/main.sh`: the runtime entrypoint you own
- `src/targets/claude/...`: authored Claude hook and packaging state

## What Gets Generated

- managed guidance files at the repo root such as `README.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`, and `GENERATED.md`
- native Claude output such as `hooks/hooks.json`

Start with this `src/README.md`, then run `plugin-kit-ai inspect . --authoring` before you expand the repo into more outputs.
{{- end }}

## Runtime

- Runtime: `{{.Runtime}}`
- Entrypoint: `{{.Entrypoint}}`
