## Bootstrap Contract

{{- if eq .Runtime "python" }}
- Runtime requirement: Python `3.10+` installed on the machine running the plugin
- Preferred runtime: project `.venv`
{{- if .SharedRuntimePackage }}
- Shared helper delivery: `plugin-kit-ai-runtime` on PyPI
- Generated dependency stub: `requirements.txt`
- Main entry imports the helper API from `plugin_kit_ai_runtime`
- Pinned runtime package version: `{{.RuntimePackageVersion}}`
{{- else }}
- Generated helper layer: `src/plugin_runtime.py`
- Generated dependency stub: `requirements.txt`
- Shared helper package: `plugin-kit-ai-runtime` on PyPI when you later want a reusable dependency instead of the vendored helper file
{{- end }}
- If `.venv` exists but is broken, `plugin-kit-ai validate --strict` will fail until you recreate it
- `plugin-kit-ai install` does not manage Python dependencies or virtualenv creation
{{- else if eq .Runtime "node" }}
- Runtime requirement: system Node.js `20+` installed on the machine running the plugin
{{- if .SharedRuntimePackage }}
- Shared helper delivery: `plugin-kit-ai-runtime` on npm
- `package.json` already declares `plugin-kit-ai-runtime`
- Main entry imports the helper API from the shared package instead of `src/plugin-runtime.*`
- Pinned runtime package version: `{{.RuntimePackageVersion}}`
{{- else }}
- Generated helper layer: `src/plugin-runtime.{{if .TypeScript}}ts{{else}}mjs{{end}}`
- Shared helper package: `plugin-kit-ai-runtime` on npm when you later want a reusable dependency instead of the vendored helper file
{{- end }}
- Commit `package-lock.json` or an equivalent deterministic lockfile for production repos
{{- if .TypeScript }}
- Generated TypeScript scaffold: `src/main.ts`, `tsconfig.json`, and built output under `dist/main.js`
- `plugin-kit-ai bootstrap .` runs `npm install` and `npm run build`
{{- else }}
- Minimal JavaScript runtime scaffold using `src/main.mjs`
- Use `plugin-kit-ai init <name> --platform claude --runtime node --typescript` when you want the built TypeScript scaffold
{{- end }}
{{- else if eq .Runtime "shell" }}
- Runtime: POSIX shell on Unix
- On Windows, this runtime requires `bash` in `PATH`
- `plugin-kit-ai install` does not package or distribute shell runtime dependencies
{{- end }}

## First Run

{{- if eq .Runtime "python" }}
```bash
plugin-kit-ai doctor .
plugin-kit-ai bootstrap .
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform claude --strict
plugin-kit-ai test . --platform claude --all
plugin-kit-ai dev . --platform claude --event Stop
```
{{- else if eq .Runtime "node" }}
```bash
plugin-kit-ai doctor .
plugin-kit-ai bootstrap .
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform claude --strict
plugin-kit-ai test . --platform claude --all
plugin-kit-ai dev . --platform claude --event Stop
```
{{- else if eq .Runtime "shell" }}
```bash
plugin-kit-ai doctor .
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform claude --strict
plugin-kit-ai test . --platform claude --all
plugin-kit-ai dev . --platform claude --event Stop
```
{{- end }}

## Stable Default

- `Stop`
- `PreToolUse`
- `UserPromptSubmit`

The scaffold wires only the public-stable Claude hook subset by default.
Treat `plugin-kit-ai validate --strict` as the CI-grade readiness gate for this plugin.
This path does not add managed dependency installation or packaged distribution for interpreted runtimes.
Choose the Go lane instead when you want downstream users to avoid installing `{{if eq .Runtime "python"}}Python{{else if eq .Runtime "node"}}Node.js{{else}}shell dependencies{{end}}` before they can run the plugin.

Use `plugin-kit-ai init <name> --platform claude --runtime {{.Runtime}} --claude-extended-hooks` when you intentionally want the full runtime-supported hook set scaffolded.

## Target Files

- `src/launcher.yaml`: runtime and entrypoint metadata for the Claude runtime lane
- `src/targets/claude/hooks/hooks.json`: authored Claude hook routing
- `hooks/hooks.json`: generated managed Claude hook file
- `fixtures/claude/*.json`: pre-generated stable Claude smoke payloads owned by this project
- `goldens/claude/*`: pre-generated stable stdout/stderr/exit contract owned by this project
{{- if eq .Runtime "python" }}
{{- if .SharedRuntimePackage }}
- `requirements.txt`: shared-helper dependency manifest for the `plugin_kit_ai_runtime` import path
{{- else }}
- `src/plugin_runtime.py`: official helper API for `on_stop`, `on_pre_tool_use`, and `on_user_prompt_submit`
{{- end }}
{{- else if eq .Runtime "node" }}
{{- if .SharedRuntimePackage }}
- `package.json`: shared-helper dependency manifest for the `plugin-kit-ai-runtime` import path
{{- else }}
- `src/plugin-runtime.{{if .TypeScript}}ts{{else}}mjs{{end}}`: official helper API for `onStop`, `onPreToolUse`, and `onUserPromptSubmit`
{{- end }}
{{- end }}
- Optional first-class Claude breadth via `--extras`:
  - `src/targets/claude/settings.json` -> generated `settings.json`
  - `src/targets/claude/lsp.json` -> generated `.lsp.json`
  - `src/targets/claude/user-config.json` -> generated `plugin.json.userConfig`
  - `src/targets/claude/manifest.extra.json` -> manifest passthrough for non-managed keys only

Keep stdout reserved for Claude responses and write diagnostics to stderr only.
